    Steps may be replayed on replan. Ensure ``http`` / ``agent`` tools are
    idempotent or carry idempotency keys. See plan_and_run_node.py.

SCAFFOLD RISK — STATE SIZE:
    Plan results accumulate in ``PlannerState.step_results`` across replans.
    Consider a summarisation step before ComposerNode and a checkpointer with
    a short TTL to limit state growth. See composer_node.py.

Graph topology
--------------
{% if planner_precheck_enabled and planner_validator_enabled and planner_composer_enabled %}
START → plan → precheck → [solver | replan→plan] → validate → [compose | replan→plan] → END
{% elif planner_precheck_enabled and planner_validator_enabled %}
START → plan → precheck → [solver | replan→plan] → validate → [END | replan→plan]
{% elif planner_precheck_enabled and planner_composer_enabled %}
START → plan → precheck → [solver | replan→plan] → compose → END
{% elif planner_validator_enabled and planner_composer_enabled %}
START → plan → solver → validate → [compose | replan→plan] → END
{% elif planner_precheck_enabled %}
START → plan → precheck → [solver | replan→plan] → END
